h1.gamma Default Notifications and Sharing
p By default, every check in on Oh Hey World will adopt the following notification and sharing settings. On a check-in by check-in basis, youâ€™ll be able to turn each on or off - these will just be filled in as defaults.
.section
  h2.epsilon
    | Notification Defaults  
  p NOTE: You can turn each of these on/off per individual check in from the check in screen.
  .text-center
    = f.fields_for :preferences do |preference|
      label class="inline-block margin-r" for="user_preferences_facebook"
        | Facebook
        = preference.check_box current_user.facebook.name, checked_preference('facebook', current_user.facebook.value)
        
      - twitter_settings_preference = (current_user.provider_valid?('twitter')) ? "" : "twitter-settings-preference"
      label class="inline-block margin-r" for="user_preferences_twitter"
        | Twitter
        = preference.check_box(current_user.twitter.name, { class: twitter_settings_preference }.merge(checked_preference('twitter', current_user.twitter.value)))
          
      label class="inline-block margin-r" for="user_preferences_sms_friends"
        | SMS
        = preference.check_box current_user.sms_friends.name, checked_preference('sms', current_user.sms_friends.value)

      label class="inline-block" for="user_preferences_email_friends"
        | Email
        = preference.check_box current_user.email_friends.name, checked_preference('email', current_user.email_friends.value)

            
              